intro: Stenanthemum intricatum, commonly known as the intricate stenanthemum, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Ericaceae and is characterized by its dense, shrub-like growth habit. The plant produces small, bell-shaped flowers that are typically pink or white in color. It thrives in well-drained soils and is often found in heathland and open forests. Due to its ornamental value, it is occasionally cultivated in gardens.
